  "texts": [
    "For example, already today, a UCITS fund \"should not invest in financial indices whose methodology for the selection and the rebalancing of the components is not based on a set of pre-determined rules and objective criteria\" according to ESMA guidelines (ESMA, 2014, par. 58).",
    "This excludes dynamically learned rules from an AI system to create an index suitable as a reference underlying.",
    "Furthermore, we expect updated regulation at the market level.",
    "The FCA report (FCA, 2018) reviews excellent and bad algorithmic trading practices.",
    "MiFID II addresses algorithmic trading, but ESMA (2021) points out \"that the use of algorithms which only serve to inform a trader of a particular investment opportunity is not considered as algorithmic trading, provided that the execution is not algorithmic\"."
